    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1192a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d26fn1">Similar telegram, on the same date, to
                        the Minister in Switzerland, No. 1401 (File No. 763.72119/1192b).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-25T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>949. Cable at earliest possible moment comments of German Socialist papers on
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCGFv1">Hertling</persName>’s address. Also comments
                    of leading Liberal organs, such as <hi rend="italic">Frankfurter Zeitung,
                        Berliner Tageblatt, Hamburger Fremdenblatt, Münchner Neueste
                        Nachrichten</hi>. Cable comments of individual papers as soon as received,
                    without waiting to present full summary. Also, if possible, obtain statement
                    from person mentioned in your cable No. 1880 of January 13<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d26fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_26">p. 26</ref>.</note> on
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCGFv1">Hertling</persName>’s address.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
